{{Infobox political party | country = Bangladesh | colorcode = black | name = Revolutionary Workers Party of Bangladesh | native_name = বাংলাদেশের বিপ্লবী ওয়ার্কার্স পার্টি | party_logo = | president = Khandaker Ali Abbas | secretary_general = Saiful Haque | foundation = 2004 | ideology = [[Marxism–Leninism]] | colours = | headquarters = 27/8/A Topkhana Road, [[Dhaka]]-1000<ref name="ecs">http://www.ecs.gov.bd/Bangla/MenuTemplate1.php?Parameter_MenuID=53</ref> | website = | symbol = }} '''Revolutionary Workers Party of Bangladesh''' is a [[political party]] in [[Bangladesh]]. The party emerged as a splinter group of [[Workers Party of Bangladesh]], and initially the party also used the name 'Workers Party of Bangladesh'.<ref>http://www.thefinancialexpress-bd.info/search_index.php?news_id=36743&page=detail_news</ref> Party president is Khandaker Ali Abbas and the general secretary is Saiful Haque. The group came out of WPB on June 14, 2004. It opposed the tactic of making joint actions together with the [[Awami League]].
Mass organisation of the party are the Bangladesh Agricultural Labour Union (BALU), Viplavi Krishak Sanhati (Revolutionary Peasants Union) and Shramjibi Nari Moitreyi (Working Women's Unity). The party publishes ''People's Democracy''.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.cpiml.org/liberation/year_2008/january/interview_with_saiful_huq.html|title= Interview with Saiful Huq<!-- Bot generated title -->}}</ref>
